ong-forgotten reading practice of cutting printed books. Proposing radical deformations to the meanings of fundamental and apparently simple terms such as “error,” “letter,” “surface,” and “cut,” Fleming opens up exciting new pathways into our understanding of writing all told.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCultural Graphology.  aJacques Derrida.  abook history.  adeconstruction.  aearly modern.  aliterature.  aprint.  apsychoanalysis.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022639042040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226390567423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226390567/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles